    "comment": "Rationale: Fig. 4 B-D shows in rat cultured cortical neurons RTN3 is colocalized with Synaptophysin at DIV 11.\n\nFigure 1 demonstrates the specificity of the anti-RTN3 antibody using Western Blot. Two bands around 30 kDa were detected in the mouse brain with anti-RTN3 serum (PMID:11990451). Bands of 25kDa and 27kDa were detected in the rat retina (lane 1) and olfactory bulb (lane 3). Both of these bands were competed for more than 99% by N14 peptide (Lane 2 & 4).. Experimental description: Adult Sprague-Dawley rats were used in the study",
